Adult.description: Northern Waterthrushes are darker brown above whereas Ovenbirds are golden-olive. They have a strong whitish eyebrow stripe and lack the Ovenbird’s eyering and strong black-and-orange crown stripes.

Louisiana Waterthrushes are darker brown than Ovenbirds, which are golden-olive above. They also have a strong white eyebrow stripe, lacking the Ovenbird’s eyering and strong black-and-orange crown stripes.

Adult (Olive-backed).description: Swainson's Thrushes are larger and lankier than Ovenbirds, with rounded heads, longer tails, and less sharply pointed bills. The breast is spotted on Swainson's but streaked on Ovenbirds.

Adult.description: Song Sparrows have thicker, conical bills instead of the Ovenbird’s straight, pointed bill. Song Sparrows also show a more complex face pattern without a white eyering or orange crown stripes.
